data.title: As Cheryl Fernandez-Versini turns 32 we chart her style transformation
data.meta_description: Cheryl Fernandez-Versini, now 32, has spent 13 years in the spotlight. Old pictures of the star are a back catalogue of every Noughties fashion trend. FEMAIL charts her best and worst style moments.
data.text:
Cheryl Fernandez-Versini turns 32 today - which means she has spent the last 13 years in the spotlight.

The X Factor judge first shot to fame in 2002 when she starred on the programme Popstars The Rivals, which formed the girl band Girls Aloud.

This means the pictures featuring the star are like a back catalogue of every Noughties fashion trend.

Scroll down for video

Whether it was boho belts, chokers with crucifixes on, bandannas, corsets or boot-cut trousers... Cheryl has worn it with pride.

The 32-year-old has long been considered a style icon.

Ever since her first stint on the X Factor, her wardrobe was highly praised by fashion critics and fans alike.

But in the years before that she struggled to find her footing, often choosing casual tracksuits over a more tailored look.

Fortunately for you - we have selected some of her best and worst sartorial moments for your viewing. To see Cheryl's style transformation over the years, read on...

Cheryl dabbled more than once in street style, with varying degrees of success.

This attempt to pull off a leather do-rag fell a bit flat.

The smoothed down hair with isolated strands at the front - check, over-sized choker - check, satin corset - check.

Cheryl took on every trend from 2002 during this appearance on Popstars The Rivals.

Who didn't wants corn rows in 2003? Along with the obligatory solitary big earring.

Cheryl's attempt at an edgy street look in 2003 didn't fare much better than her do-rag six months earlier.

Girls Aloud performed at G-A-Y in May 2003 and Cheryl went all out with that summer's fashion trends.

The visible G-string, tramp stamp tattoo and colourful sports band were all big that season.

CD-UK was one of the biggest TV shows of the early Noughties, so it's only right that Cheryl embraced the look of the moment for Girls Aloud;'s appearance on the programme.

Who didn't sport a quiff, large hoop earrings and an off-the-shoulder distressed sweater in 2004?

For T In the Park in 2004, Cheryl went for the matching accessories look that was popular at the time.

The colourful material skater belts with silver hoops were seen on teenage girls across the country, as were the bright plastic hooped earrings, and Jennifer-Lopez style coloured sunglasses (although Cheryl's are missing the obligatory diamante heart in the corner).

More of the matching looking for an appearance at G-A-Y to promote the new Girls Aloud single in June 2004.

Also making an appearance were the bakers cap and the diamante Premiership footballer-style diamante crucifix that was so popular at the time.

In 2005, the boho chic trend had started to take hold and Cheryl was one of millions of young women sporting brown studded belts like the one she wore at a Childline Concert in Dublin and the Fox FM party in London.

The French manicure, distressed denim, trucker hats, furry gilets and customised American Vintage T-shirts were also popular that year.

By the mid-Noughties the fashion for overly fake-tanned skin was in full swing and Cheryl was no exception, as is proved by this picture of her at the Brit Awards in 2005.

The chandelier earrings and diamante heart pendant were also key jewellery trends that year.

In 2006, it was tough to find a celebrity that hadn't succumbed to the velour tracksuit trend - Cheryl was no exception.

In a double whammy of Noughties style, she also topped off her look with a Von Dutch style trucker cap.

These days, no woman would be seen dead showing off her T-shirt bra... back in 2006 it was another matter altogether.

She completed the look with of-the-moment slouched brown boots with bare legs and a baguette bag.

Cheryl and Ashley Cole will forever regret the day that they signed up for this National Lottery shoot.

Everything from Ashley's bling to Cheryl's ruffle miniskirt screams 2006.

At the 2006 World Cup, Cheryl Cole put her best fashion foot forward as she was sat next to Victoria Beckham for most of the tournament.

Sadly, the trends of the time meant that consisted of an over-sized colourful 80s-style belt cinched around a white bandeau top, paired with denim micro-pants.

Who didn't love pinstripes in 2006?

To make the look even more 'of the moment', Cheryl also wore bootlegged trousers on her suit at the World Charity Premiere of Its A Boy Girl in London's Leicester Square.

By 2007, Cheryl had really found her fashion footing.

An elegant fringed long bob completed her new sophisticated style.

By 2008 at the Brit Awards, Cheryl's signature hairdo was fully-formed.

Apart from a few brief style changes, the popstar's highlighted, heavily extensions and curled look has been her fail safe hairstyle.

2008 was Cheryl's first year on the X Factor.

The appointment to the ITV reality show, alongside Simon Cowell and Louis Walsh, saw a dramatic change in her style, into polished nation's sweetheart.

While most women would struggle to look stylish while climbing a mountain, Cheryl managed it with ease.

The singer look unflustered as she took part in the BT Red Nose Climb of Kilimanjaro in 2009.

While the rest of Girls Aloud opted for OTT gowns for the 2009 Brit Awards, Cheryl picked a Georges Chakra daisy number.

Accessorised with a red lip, she fully mastered the red carpet look.

In 2009, Cheryl Cole landed a deal to front beauty brand L'Oreal Paris.

That same year, she was voted the World's Sexiest Woman by FHM.

As Cheryl Cole unveiled her waxwork at Madame Tussauds in London in 2010, she showed off the effects of her L'Oreal Feria hair colouring.

Her outfit for the evening was the perfect combination of fun and edgy for the event.

At Cannes in 2010, Cheryl made sure all eyes were on her with a long wavy bob.

Her cream gown was a big hit with fashion critics, although it was slightly marred by a flashing of her thigh tattoo.

After Kate Middleton made them the shoe of 2010, few women failed to purchase a pair of nude courts in 2011.

Cheryl was no exception and wore hers to the Brit Awards in 2011.

After moving to the US for the X Factor in 2011, Cheryl appeared to lose all sense of style.

The singer's bouffant hairstyle was likened to that of Chewbacca and her bizarre outfit was commented on across the western world.

After she was dropped from the US X Factor, Cheryl refused to lie low.

The singer changed her look by dyeing her hair blonde and cutting it into a bob, then making several high profile red carpet appearances, like here at the Pride Of Britain Awards in November, 2011.

BY 2012, Cheryl was back to her signature dark brown mane and was becoming increasingly bold with her wardrobe choices.

For the Diamond Jubilee in 2012, she opted for a dramatic sequinned dress by Polish designer Ewa Minge.

2012 was also the year that Cheryl Cole made her debut in a Hollywood film.

She upped the glamour stakes and outshone Cameron Diaz at the European premiere of 'What to expect when you are Expecting', in London that May.

In 2012, Cheryl's daytime look has also become polished.

Her appearance at the Capital FM Summertime Ball was faultless.

Stage costumes follow a different rule to everyday clothing, but even so, Cheryl's outfit here gets a big thumbs down.

The singer opted for OTT everything when she performed on the opening night of her 'A Million Lights' tour at The Odyssey Arena in Belfast, Northern Ireland, in October 2012.

Cheryl suffered a bizarre wardrobe fail for the publicity shots of her return to X Factor UK in 2014.

The singer wore a strange electric blue jumpsuit that wouldn't have looked out of place on an ice skater.

Cheryl had found her fashion footing again by the time it came to film the Judges' Houses round of X Factor in August 2014.

She looked elegant in a boho white dress, complete with mirrored sunglasses.

Since Cheryl became Mrs Fernandez-Versini her style has been overhauled.

As well as a chic bob, the single has taken to wearing gamine dresses.

At the Cannes film festival this year, her look was the most sophisticated yet.
